## ✅ Lunch Break Feature Implementation Complete

### **New Features Added:**

#### **1. Database Schema Updates**
- **lunch_start_timestamp** (string, optional) - Records when lunch break starts
- **lunch_end_timestamp** (string, optional) - Records when lunch break ends  
- **lunch_duration_minutes** (number, optional) - Total lunch time in minutes

#### **2. Employee View - Lunch Break Controls**

**When Clocked In (Not on Lunch):**
- Two-button layout: "Start Lunch Break" (outline) and "Clock Out" (destructive red)
- Coffee icon on lunch button
- Shows accumulated lunch time if any breaks were taken earlier
- Location and work description fields remain visible and editable

**When On Lunch Break:**
- Orange banner replaces green "Currently Clocked In" banner
- Coffee icon prominently displayed
- Shows "On Lunch Break" status with start timestamp
- Single full-width button: "End Lunch Break"
- Location and work description fields hidden during lunch
- Real-time timer pauses (doesn't count lunch time)

**After Ending Lunch:**
- Returns to normal clocked-in state
- Lunch duration is accumulated (supports multiple lunch breaks per shift)
- Lunch time is displayed in the green status banner
- Employee can start another lunch break if needed

#### **3. Automatic Time Calculations**

**Total Hours Worked:**
- Calculated as: (Clock Out - Clock In) - Lunch Duration
- Lunch time automatically deducted from total hours
- Supports multiple lunch breaks (durations are summed)
- Example: 8 hour shift with 45 min lunch = 7.25 hours paid

**Lunch Duration Display:**
- Shown in minutes (e.g., "45 min")
- Visible in employee history and manager dashboard
- Appears in active shift status when not on lunch

#### **4. Time Card History Updates**

**New Column Added:**
- "Lunch" column showing lunch duration in minutes
- Displays "—" if no lunch was taken
- Rounded to nearest minute for clean display

**Status Badges:**
- Orange "On Lunch Break" badge when actively on lunch
- Green "Active" badge when working
- Gray "Completed" badge when shift is done

